div.div:
Fix: Correctly display event end time in admin email
The ScheduleMail class has been updated to correctly parse and display the end time of scheduled events using Carbon in admin emails. By using Carbon's parse method, the end time is now formatted in a reader-friendly manner. This adjustment improves the overall presentation and readability of schedule information in email notifications sent to admins.

PATCH: Add: ScheduleMail class and email notification feature
Added a new ScheduleMail class to handle email notifications related to event schedules. It queries for events in different status (incoming, started, finished) for the current month and year. On updating events, the system can now send these schedule notifications to a list of users. Modifications were also made in email view files to improve schedule presentation.

Fix: Correct user power comparison logic in UserEditScreen
Fixed an issue in UserEditScreen where the larger user power comparison logic was inverted. The corrected code now prevents unauthorized termination of a user by another user with lesser power, thus enhancing the security of user management.

PATCH: Refactor code and introduce additional permissions in routes
Refactored the web routes and introduced permission checks for various API routes. Additionally, expanded the middleware to handle the permission checks during the request processing. These improvements increase the security layer by ensuring users can only access routes they have permissions for.

Refactor: Simplify UserEditLayout fields and remove unused code
Simplified the fields() function in UserEditLayout by removing unused code and redundant checks. Also, stopped constructing avatar URLs in the Picture field, since it's now handled by the 'Cropper' field. These changes enhance code readability and maintainability as well as improving data integrity.
